```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 600 height: 300 background: '(250 245 240))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((frame 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (let* ((t (modulo (/ frame 120.0) 1.0))
              (x (+ 100 (* 400 t)))
              (gap-center 300)
              (gap-width 80)
              (in-gap (and (> x (- gap-center gap-width)) (< x (+ gap-center gap-width))))
              (squash (if in-gap
                          (let ((gap-t (/ (- x (- gap-center gap-width)) (* 2.0 gap-width))))
                            (- 1.0 (* 0.6 (sin (* gap-t 3.14)))))
                          1.0))
              (h-scale (/ 1.0 (sqrt squash)))
              (v-scale (sqrt squash)))
         (world-draw-rect w 290 100 20 100 '(120 120 120) 'fill)
         (world-draw-rect w 290 0 20 90 '(120 120 120) 'fill)
         (world-draw-ellipse w x 150
                             (* 35 h-scale)
                             (* 35 v-scale)
                             '(200 120 80) 'fill)
         (set! frame (+ frame 1))))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

[VISUAL: An orange ellipse sliding horizontally, compressing vertically as it passes through a narrow gap between two gray bars.]

