### Accordion fold: multiple segments squashing in phase

Simulating a segmented creature compressing like a bellows.

```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 500 height: 400 background: '(245 245 250))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((frame 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (let* ((t (/ frame 60.0))
              (squash (+ 0.7 (* 0.3 (sin (* t 3.0))))))
         (let loop ((i 0))
           (when (< i 6)
             (let* ((x (+ 100 (* i 65)))
                    (h-scale (/ 1.0 (sqrt squash)))
                    (v-scale (sqrt squash)))
               (world-draw-ellipse w x 200 (* 30 h-scale) (* 40 v-scale)
                                   (if (even? i) '(180 100 100) '(100 180 100)) 'fill))
             (loop (+ i 1)))))
       (set! frame (+ frame 1)))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

[VISUAL: Six ellipses in a row—alternating red and green—all squashing and stretching in unison.]

