### Elastic snap-back

Overstretched object that recoils violently.

```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 400 height: 400 background: '(245 250 245))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((frame 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (let* ((cycle (modulo (/ frame 100.0) 1.0))
              (stretch (cond
                        ((< cycle 0.4) (+ 1.0 (* 1.2 (/ cycle 0.4))))
                        ((< cycle 0.5) (- 2.2 (* 3.0 (/ (- cycle 0.4) 0.1))))
                        ((< cycle 0.6) (+ 0.8 (* 0.6 (/ (- cycle 0.5) 0.1))))
                        ((< cycle 0.7) (- 1.4 (* 0.5 (/ (- cycle 0.6) 0.1))))
                        (else 1.0)))
              (h-scale (sqrt stretch))
              (v-scale (/ 1.0 (sqrt stretch))))
         (world-draw-ellipse w 200 200
                             (* 50 h-scale)
                             (* 50 v-scale)
                             '(100 180 160) 'fill)
         (set! frame (+ frame 1))))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

[VISUAL: A teal ellipse stretching wide, then snapping back with overshoot oscillations before settling.]

