### Layered squash: foreground and background at different rates

Two objects at different depths squashing with parallax timing.

```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 500 height: 400 background: '(250 248 245))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((frame 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (let* ((t (/ frame 60.0))
              (back-squash (+ 0.8 (* 0.2 (sin (* t 2.0)))))
              (front-squash (+ 0.7 (* 0.3 (sin (* t 2.8)))))
              (bh (* 60 (/ 1.0 (sqrt back-squash))))
              (bv (* 60 (sqrt back-squash)))
              (fh (* 50 (/ 1.0 (sqrt front-squash))))
              (fv (* 50 (sqrt front-squash))))
         (world-draw-ellipse w 350 200 bh bv '(180 180 200) 'fill)
         (world-draw-ellipse w 200 200 fh fv '(220 140 100) 'fill)
         (set! frame (+ frame 1))))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

