### Squash during drag

User drags an object; it squashes in the direction of motion.

*[needs: mouse drag input]*

```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 500 height: 400 background: '(245 250 245))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((x 250) (y 200) (vx 0) (vy 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (set! vx (* vx 0.95))
       (set! vy (* vy 0.95))
       (set! x (+ x vx))
       (set! y (+ y vy))
       (let* ((speed (sqrt (+ (* vx vx) (* vy vy))))
              (stretch (+ 1.0 (* 0.1 speed)))
              (h-scale (sqrt stretch))
              (v-scale (/ 1.0 (sqrt stretch))))
         (world-draw-ellipse w x y
                             (* 40 h-scale)
                             (* 40 v-scale)
                             '(100 180 140) 'fill)))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

