### Variable stiffness: hard vs. soft squash

Two objects with different squash responsiveness.

```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 500 height: 300 background: '(250 248 245))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((frame 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (let* ((t (/ frame 60.0))
              (force (sin (* t 3.0)))
              (hard-squash (+ 0.9 (* 0.1 force)))
              (soft-squash (+ 0.6 (* 0.4 force)))
              (h-hard (* 40 (/ 1.0 (sqrt hard-squash))))
              (v-hard (* 40 (sqrt hard-squash)))
              (h-soft (* 40 (/ 1.0 (sqrt soft-squash))))
              (v-soft (* 40 (sqrt soft-squash))))
         (world-draw-ellipse w 200 150 h-hard v-hard '(120 120 140) 'fill)
         (world-draw-ellipse w 350 150 h-soft v-soft '(200 140 140) 'fill)
         (set! frame (+ frame 1))))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

[VISUAL: Two ellipses side-by-side; the gray one barely squashes, the pink one deforms dramatically under the same \"force.\"]

