### Compound motion: squash + oscillation

A bouncing ball with both height oscillation and squash-stretch.

```scheme
(call-with-world
 (make-world width: 400 height: 500 background: '(245 245 250))
 (lambda (w)
   (let ((frame 0))
     (define (draw)
       (world-clear w)
       (let* ((t (/ frame 60.0))
              (bounce-cycle (- t (floor t)))
              (y (+ 100 (* 300 (expt (- (* 2.0 bounce-cycle) 1.0) 2.0))))
              (vy (* 600 2.0 (- (* 2.0 bounce-cycle) 1.0) (/ 1.0 60.0)))
              (contact (> y 380))
              (squash (if contact 0.5 (+ 1.0 (* 0.015 (abs vy)))))
              (h-scale (/ 1.0 (sqrt squash)))
              (v-scale (sqrt squash)))
         (world-draw-ellipse w 200 (min y 400)
                             (* 40 h-scale)
                             (* 40 v-scale)
                             '(200 120 100) 'fill)
         (set! frame (+ frame 1))))
     (world-on-tick w draw 60)
     (world-show w)
     (world-wait w))))
```

[VISUAL: An orange ball bouncing in a parabolic arc, stretching during flight, squashing hard at the floor.]

